{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix HandoverRequest handling in NGAP gNB decoder\n\n### Summary\nThe NGAP gNB module was unable to process incoming HandoverRequest messages from the AMF due to missing decoder support for the HandoverResourceAllocation procedure. When a HandoverRequest was received, the decoder would hit an unhandled procedure code case and trigger a fatal assertion, causing the gNB to crash.\n\nAdditionally, the expected `decode_ng_handover_request()` function mentioned in user code was not implemented, leading to linker errors when trying to decode HandoverRequest messages directly.\n\nThe fix implements proper handling for HandoverResourceAllocation procedure codes in the NGAP decoder and adds the missing `decode_ng_handover_request()` function. A handler function for HandoverRequest messages has also been added to process these messages appropriately.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_decoder.c`: Added case for `NGAP_ProcedureCode_id_HandoverResourceAllocation` in `ngap_gNB_decode_initiating_message` and implemented `decode_ng_handover_request()` function\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_decoder.h`: Added function prototype for `decode_ng_handover_request()`\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_handlers.c`: Added `ngap_gNB_handle_handover_request()` handler function and updated handler table\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_handlers.h`: Added function prototype for `ngap_gNB_handle_handover_request()`\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_common.h`: Added conditional include for `NGAP_HandoverRequest.h`\n\n"
}